{
  "id": "ex_technical_2089c602",
  "intent": "Execute a Nextera XT library preparation protocol with dual indexing PCR. Begin with genomic DNA amplification using 21\u00b5L Phusion master mix and 2\u00b5L DNA template, followed by touchdown PCR (98\u00b0C initial denaturation, then 10 cycles decreasing annealing temperature from 69\u00b0C to 60\u00b0C, plus 25 cycles at 72\u00b0C). Perform magnetic bead purification with 45\u00b5L beads, dual ethanol washes at 150\u00b5L, and elution in 40\u00b5L water. Execute indexing PCR using 17.5\u00b5L KAPA master mix with 2.5\u00b5L each of north and south indexing primers, followed by standard PCR cycling (95\u00b0C denaturation, 55\u00b0C annealing, 72\u00b0C extension for 12 cycles). Complete with final magnetic bead cleanup.",
